Squeeze spinach to remove liquid. With a mixer, beat spinach, mayonnaise, cream cheese, onion, garlic, 1 cup of the parmesan cheese, and pepper until thoroughly combined. Mound mixture in a 3- to 4-cup baking dish. Sprinkle evenly with 2 tablespoons parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake in a 350 degrees F oven until hot in center and lightly browned on top, 25 to 30 minutes. Serve hot to spread on baguette slices.